setup_purgatory \- initialize the purgatory's global variables
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" setup_purgatory
.BI "(struct kimage *image "  ","
.BI "const void *slave_code "  ","
.BI "const void *fdt "  ","
.BI "unsigned long kernel_load_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long fdt_load_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "image" 12
kexec image.
.IP "slave_code" 12
Slave code for the purgatory.
.IP "fdt" 12
Flattened device tree for the next kernel.
.IP "kernel_load_addr" 12
Address where the kernel is loaded.
.IP "fdt_load_addr" 12
Address where the flattened device tree is loaded.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or negative errno on error.
